Description: Think Tank and Go to Market
Full Description: Multi-Cloud Leadership Alliance Mission: To bring together business development professionals to share best practices for partnering with Cloud Solution Providers (CSPs). The Multi-Cloud Leadership Alliance is a change agent and influencing body for ISVs, MSPs, and others dealing with Azure, AWS, and Google Cloud Platform. We are a voice all working together to foster collaboration and influence change within the ecosystem to better serve our customers and grow our revenue within the ecosystem.   Why would we share best practices? Aren’t we all just competing for mindshare with the public cloud vendors? Not at all. By sharing best practices, we can become the trusted advisor to our enterprise customers. Further, we can collaborate to understand our customers’ challenges and become an influencing body to the CSPs.   Market Background: Large and small enterprises are adopting multi-cloud strategies to meet the demands of their customers and to achieve operational excellence. ISVs, infrastructure vendors and the vast range of channel partners including systems integrators (SIs), value added resellers (VARs) and managed service providers (MSPs) must partner with CSPs to provide their customers the best experience and support.  Sales, business development and marketing leaders lack the knowledge when it comes to working with the Cloud Service Providers – whether AWS, Azure or GCP. The Multi-Cloud Leadership Alliance will serve the market need to establish a consortium and provide one source of truth to share best practices with each other and influence change with CSPs.

(Some firms only run local court background checks, and contractors sometimes have no background checks at all.)         In addition to a background check, all of our employees have their background monitored throughout their employment so if something new happens, we will be notified immediately.         Our professionals always work in teams of two or three both for their own safety and to ensure the job is done efficiently and correctly.         Our professionals are always easily identifiable by their uniforms, so you know who is entering your home (trainees may not yet have uniforms). Insurance We carry two million dollars in liability insurance covering breakage or any other damage that may occur in your home. (Firms using contractors often claim to be insured, but they may only be insuring themselves and not the actual contractors who are supposed to carry their own insurance. Very often, the contractors are uninsured.) We provide workers compensation insurance for our employees, so if they are injured on the job, they are well taken care of. This is not required in Texas, and most of our competitors do not offer this, but we believe it is important to both protect our employees and protect you from any claims should an employee be injured in your home. (Once again, contractors are rarely covered by this type of insurance.)
